{"id":801,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":801,"title":"Lucifer","subtitle":"","short_title":"Lucifer","uri":"/scriptures/bd/lucifer","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/lucifer.t1","order":".000.2110"},[".title","Lucifer"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/lucifer.p1","order":".000.2111"},"Literally",["i","the Shining One;"],"also",["i","Lightbringer"],"or",["i","Son of the Morning."],"Lucifer is also known as Satan or the devil. The name Lucifer appears only once in the Bible (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/isa/14.12"},"Isa. 14:12"],"; compare",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/10.18"},"Luke 10:18"],"). Apparently Lucifer is the name of the devil before his rebellion and fall. Latter-day revelation clarifies the fall of Lucifer and equates him with Satan (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/76.25-38"},"D&C 76:25–38"],"; see also",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rev/12"},"Rev. 12"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/9.8"},"2 Ne. 9:8"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/29.36-38"},"D&C 29:36–38"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/4.1-4"},"Moses 4:1–4"],")."]]],"refs":null}
